Sentencas: Co-Ni and 5% Fe doping Co-Ni alloy coatings are prepared on SUS 430 substrates as interconnect protect layers for solid oxide fuel cells by electroplating.
Titulo: Effect of Fe on the oxidation behavior, electrical properties and microstructure of Co-Ni protective coatings for metal interconnect layers in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical characteristics and oxidation resistance of interconnects are enhanced by the alloy coatings after they are oxidized in air at 800 degrees C for 1000 h and the Co-NiFe alloy coatings showing the better effect.
Titulo: Effect of Fe on the oxidation behavior, electrical properties and microstructure of Co-Ni protective coatings for metal interconnect layers in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Cr is unable to diffuse outward owing to the multi-layer oxidation structure.
Titulo: Effect of Fe on the oxidation behavior, electrical properties and microstructure of Co-Ni protective coatings for metal interconnect layers in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Addition of Fe to Co-Ni alloy coatings leads to the formation of a (Fe,Co,Ni)3O4 spinel layer with lower activation energy and stronger ability to restrict oxygen diffusion inward.
Titulo: Effect of Fe on the oxidation behavior, electrical properties and microstructure of Co-Ni protective coatings for metal interconnect layers in solid oxide fuel cells
